# Professional HTML Content Rules

## 🚫 No Emojis Policy
- **NEVER** use emojis in HTML content, titles, or text
- **REPLACE** emoji usage with professional icon elements
- **MAINTAIN** professional appearance throughout

## 🎯 Professional Content Standards
- Use proper semantic HTML5 elements
- Implement consistent heading hierarchy
- Apply professional typography
- Use descriptive alt text for images
- Maintain accessibility standards

## 🔄 Emoji Replacement Examples
```html
<!-- ❌ WRONG: Using emojis -->
<h4>⚡ Performance Metrics</h4>
<div class="data-card">
    <h4>🏗️ Families Analysis</h4>
</div>

<!-- ✅ CORRECT: Using professional icons -->
<h4><img src="asset/icon/performance.png" alt="Performance" class="icon icon-20 icon-with-text">Performance Metrics</h4>
<div class="data-card">
    <h4><img src="asset/icon/data.png" alt="Families" class="icon icon-20 icon-with-text icon-invert">Families Analysis</h4>
</div>
```

## 📋 Icon Implementation Standards
- Use consistent icon sizing: `icon-16`, `icon-20`, `icon-24`
- Apply proper alt text for accessibility
- Use `icon-with-text` class for inline icons
- Apply `icon-invert` for dark backgrounds
- Maintain consistent icon styling

## 🎨 Professional Styling
- Use CSS variables for consistent colors
- Apply proper spacing and margins
- Implement consistent border styling
- Use professional color schemes
- Maintain clean, readable layouts